    "summary": "Somalia's electoral commission has set July 25 as the deadline for political party registration and July 30 for candidate nominations in Galmudug local council elections, marking a key step in the country's electoral transition.",
    "content": "Somalia's National Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (NIEBC) has announced a July 25 deadline for political parties to register for upcoming local council elections in the central state of Galmudug, with candidate nominations closing on July 30. The announcement was made from the regional capital, Dhusamareeb, on Tuesday.\n\nThe elections are part of a broader federal initiative to replace Somalia's traditional clan-based power-sharing system with direct democratic representation. Galmudug's polls are seen as a critical test for this transition, as the country moves toward universal suffrage after decades of indirect voting.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, these local elections represent a tangible step toward inclusive governance in their homeland. Successful implementation could encourage broader political participation and stability, potentially opening avenues for diaspora engagement in future electoral processes.\n\nObservers will closely watch the registration and nomination process as an indicator of the commission's capacity to manage transparent polls. The timeline requires swift action from political actors, signaling urgency in advancing the electoral calendar.\n\nRead the original report from Radio Dalsan here: https://radiodalsan.com/2026/07/23/electoral-commission-sets-july-25-deadline-for-galmudug-elections/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=electoral-commission-sets-july-25-deadline-for-galmudug-elections",
